Northeast Corridor Train Service Resumes After New Jersey Transformer Fire

-- B y   M a r k   C l o t h i e r
-- 
2011-06-21T12:36:01Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-21/northeast-corridor-train-service-resumes-after-new-jersey-transformer-fire.html
Northeast Corridor train service
resumed as of 6:45 a.m. after a fire at a  New Brunswick 
substation,  New Jersey Transit said . There will be 10-minute to
15-minute delays in service.  The service disruption was caused by a fire at an
electrical substation in New Brunswick,  New Jersey , Penny Bassett Hackett, a spokeswoman for New Jersey Transit, said in a
telephone interview. The cause of the fire is being
investigated, Amtrak said on its website.  Trains between Philadelphia and New York are running at
reduced speed in both directions because of the earlier outage,
Amtrak said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Mark Clothier in Atlanta at 
